{{Infobox recurring event |name = Dia dos Namorados |native_name = |native_name_lang = |logo = |logo_alt = |logo_caption = |logo_size = |alt = |caption = |status = <!-- e.g. defunct, active, inactive ... --> |genre = <!-- e.g. natural phenomena, fairs, festivals, conferences, exhibitions ... --> |date = June 12 |begins = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> |ends = <!-- {{end date|YYYY|mm|dd}} --> |frequency = Annually |venue = |location = |coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:event|display=inline,title}} --> |country = Brazil - Portugal |years_active = <!-- {{age|YYYY|mm|dd}} Date of the first occurrence --> |first = <!-- {{start date|YYYY|mm|dd}} "founded=" and "established=" also work --> |founder_name = <!-- or | founders = --> |last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |prev = |next = |participants = |attendance = |capacity = |area = |budget = |activity = |leader_name = |patron = |organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> |filing = |people = |member = |sponsor = <!-- | or sponsors = --> |website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> |footnotes = }}
{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}} '''Dia dos Namorados''' ({{IPA-pt|ˈdʒiɐ duʒ namoˈɾaduʃ|lang}}, ''Lovers' Day'') is celebrated on June 12 in Brazil, due to the date's proximity to Saint Anthony's Day on June 13. The date is celebrated in a manner similar to the way that [[Valentine's Day]] is celebrated on February 14 in many other parts of the world, with gifts, [[Romance (love)|romantic activities]], decorations and festivities. The term "Dia dos Namorados" is also used in other [[CPLP|Portuguese-speaking countries]].
==Background== [[Anthony of Padua]], known as Saint Anthony, died on June 13, 1231, in Padua, Italy.<ref name=OC>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholicculture.org/culture/liturgicalyear/calendar/day.cfm?date=2013-06-13|title=Old Calendar: St. Anthony of Padua|accessdate=June 25, 2013|date=|publisher=Trinity Communications}}</ref> In addition to having been [[Canonization|canonized]] as a [[saint]] by the [[Catholic Church]], Anthony of Padua is recognized as a [[General officer|general]] in the [[Brazilian Army]].<ref name=OC/> In [[Brazil]], the Dia dos Namorados is celebrated on June 12, which is Saint Anthony's Day Eve.<ref name=DDNADFTE>{{cite web|url=http://www.boldsky.com/insync/pulse/2007/brazilian-couple.html|title=Dia Dos Namorados – A Day For The Enamoured|accessdate=June 18, 2013|date=January 31, 2007|work=[[Bold Sky]]|publisher=[[Oneindia.in]]}}</ref> Saint Anthony is recognized for blessing young couples with happy and prosperous marriages.<ref name=DDNADFTE/> Celebrations for Dia dos Namorados in Brazil and those for Valentine's Day in most other countries are similar. Typically, couples exchange romantic gifts, such as chocolates or flowers, and they may also share a "date night".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://riotimesonline.com/brazil-news/rio-entertainment/celebrate-dia-dos-namorados-in-rio/|title=Celebrate Dia dos Namorados 2013 in Rio|accessdate=June 12, 2013|date=June 11, 2013|work=[[Rio Times]]|author=Fiona Hurrell}}</ref> Additionally, beautifying home decorations are common as a part of the celebration. The day is festive, with colorful street decorations, parades and carnivals. Common musical celebrations include [[samba]] dancing and other folk music celebrations.<ref name=DDNADFTE/> In 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/doodles/dia-dos-namorados-2011|title=Dia Dos Namorados 2011|accessdate=June 12, 2014|date=June 12, 2011|publisher=[[Google]]}}</ref> and in 2012,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/doodles/dia-dos-namorados-2012|title=Dia Dos Namorados 2012|accessdate=June 12, 2013|date=June 12, 2012|publisher=[[Google]]}}</ref> the day was recognized online as the subject of a [[Google doodle]].
Dia dos Namorados as a celebration for lovers is closely related to observances of Saint Anthony's Day. Although Saint Anthony's Day is celebrated in some countries on January 17 in association with [[Anthony the Great]],<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=d29Yo-UIBSwC&pg=PA1491&dq=Saint+Anthony%27s+Day+Marriage&hl=en&sa=X&ei=K4vKUfypHIbN0AH61IHYBw&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Saint%20Anthony%27s%20Day%20Marriage&f=false|title=Encyclopædia of Superstitions, Folklore, and the Occult Sciences of the World|accessdate=June 26, 2013|date=2003|isbn=1410209164|publisher=[[University Press of the Pacific]]|page=1491|editor= Daniels, Cora Linn and C. M. Stevans|volume=III}}</ref> Saint Anthony (of Padua)'s Day Eve or Saint Anthony's Day is a [[feast day|day of religious observance]] for many in Brazil and his homeland of Portugal.<ref name=RC>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KDU30Ae4S4cC&pg=PA41&dq=Saint+Anthony%27s+Day+Feast+day+June+13&hl=en&sa=X&ei=Qo_KUZ3pNsS90AHTwYDoCw&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=Saint%20Anthony%27s%20Day%20Feast%20day%20June%2013&f=false|title=Religious Celebrations: An Encyclopedia of Holidays, Festivals, Solemn Observances, and Spiritual Commemorations|accessdate=June 26, 2013|date=2011|isbn=1598842056|publisher=[[ABC-CLIO]]|author=|pages=40&ndash;41}}</ref> Single women perform popular rituals, called ''simpatias'', in order to find a good husband or boyfriend.<!-- Source is not an [[WP:RS]] One such custom is to write the names of potential boyfriends on three pieces of paper and place them under one's pillow. The first name drawn upon awakening is believed to be the destined boyfriend. More aggressive tactics include turning St. Anthony's picture upside down behind a door on this day. until a suitor arrived.<ref name=DDNVDiB>{{cite web|url=http://gobrazil.about.com/b/2010/06/12/dia-dos-namorados-valentines-day-in-brazil.htm|title=Dia dos Namorados, Valentine's Day in Brazil|accessdate=June 12, 2013|date=June 12, 2010|publisher=[[About.com]]|author=Ribeiro, Patricia}}</ref>--> In addition to prayer on the Eve, one might conceal a love letter in a pot of basil to pass to a prospective suitor.<ref name=RC/>
The February 14 Valentine's Day is not celebrated in Brazil at all because it usually falls close to the [[Brazilian Carnival]], which is celebrated in most other countries annually during the four days before [[Ash Wednesday]], which falls between February 4 and March 10 depending on the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,900628,00.html|title=The Psychology of Carnaval|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=February 14, 1969|accessdate=June 12, 2013}}</ref> <!-- The June 12 holiday celebration was popularized in the 1950 by an advertising professional.--><!--(Unable to find an [[WP:RS]] for the following) Dia dos Namorados' June 12 recognition traces back to 1949 when the São Paulo Chamber of Commerce originated the date in hopes of boosting commercial activity during its traditional cyclical lull period.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madeinbrazilbbq.com/valentines-day-dia-dos-namorados|title=Valentine’s Day / Dia dos Namorados|accessdate=June 18, 2013|date=|publisher=MadeInBrazilbbq.com}}</ref>-->
In other Portuguese speaking countries, mainly in Africa, Valentine's Day is referred to as "Dia dos Namorados" and celebrated the same day Valentine's Day is celebrated in February.{{citation needed|date=July 2013}}
