{{Infobox NRHP | name = Dougherty Auditorium | nrhp_type = | image = Farris theater.jpg | caption = Farris theater postcard image | location= 203 W. Main St., [[Richmond, Missouri]] | coordinates={{coord|39|16|42|N|93|58|45|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Missouri#USA | built = {{Start date|1900}}-1901 | architect = Shepard & Farrar | added = September 16, 1982 | area = less than one acre | refnum = 82003158<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
'''Dougherty Auditorium''', also known as '''Farris Theater''', is a historic [[theatre]] located at [[Richmond, Missouri|Richmond]], [[Ray County, Missouri]]. It was built in 1900-1901, and is a two-story, rectangular brick building measuring 60 feet by 100 feet. It features a [[Palladian window]] of sheet metal above the central entrance with flanking circular windows.<ref name="DNR">{{cite web| url =http://dnr.mo.gov/shpo/nps-nr/82003158.pdf| title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Dougherty Auditorium | accessdate = 2017-02-01| author=Sherry Piland and James M. Denny|format = PDF| date=March 1979|publisher=Missouri Department of Natural Resources}} (includes 7 photographs from 1981)</ref>{{rp|2-3}} It currently houses a local history museum.
It was added to the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1979.<ref name="nris"/>
