==Events== * [[314]] &ndash; [[Pope Sylvester I]] succeeds [[Pope Miltiades]]. *[[1208]] &ndash; [[Battle of Lena]] takes place. *[[1504]] &ndash; The Treaty of Lyon ends the [[Italian War of 1499–1504|Italian War]], confirming French domination of northern Italy, while Spain receives the [[Kingdom of Naples]]. *[[1578]] &ndash; The [[Battle of Gembloux (1578)|Battle of Gembloux]] takes place. *[[1606]] &ndash; [[Gunpowder Plot]]: [[Guy Fawkes]] is executed for plotting against [[Parliament of England|Parliament]] and [[James VI and I|King James]]. *[[1747]] &ndash; The first [[venereal disease]]s clinic opens at [[London Lock Hospital]]. *[[1801]] &ndash; [[John Marshall]] is appointed the [[Chief Justice of the United States]]. *[[1814]] &ndash; [[Gervasio Antonio de Posadas]] becomes [[Supreme Director of the United Provinces of the Río de la Plata]] (present-day Argentina). *[[1846]] &ndash; After the [[Milwaukee Bridge War]], Juneautown and Kilbourntown unify as the City of [[Milwaukee]]. *[[1848]] &ndash; [[John C. Frémont]] is [[court-martial]]ed for mutiny and disobeying orders. *[[1862]] &ndash; [[Alvan Graham Clark]] discovers the [[white dwarf]] star Sirius B, a companion of [[Sirius]], through an {{convert|18.5|in|cm|adj=on}} telescope now located at [[Northwestern University]]. *[[1865]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: The [[United States Congress]] passes the [[Thirteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution]], abolishing slavery and submits it to the states for ratification. * 1865 &ndash; American Civil War: [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] General [[Robert E. Lee]] becomes general-in-chief. *[[1891]] &ndash; [[History of Portugal (1834–1910)|History of Portugal]]: The first attempt at a Portuguese [[republicanism|republican]] revolution breaks out in the northern city of [[Porto]]. *[[1897]] &ndash; [[Czechoslovak Trade Union Association|Czechoslav Trade Union Association]] is founded in [[Prague]]. *[[1900]] &ndash; Datu Muhammad Salleh is killed in Kampung Teboh, Tambunan, ending the [[Mat Salleh Rebellion]]. *[[1915]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: [[German Empire|Germany]] is the first to make large-scale use of [[Chemical weapons in World War I|poison gas]] in warfare in the [[Battle of Bolimów]] against [[Russian Empire|Russia]]. *[[1917]] &ndash; World War I: Germany announces that its [[U-boat]]s will [[U-boat Campaign (World War I)|resume unrestricted submarine warfare]] after a two-year hiatus. *[[1918]] &ndash; A [[Battle of May Island|series of accidental collisions]] on a misty Scottish night leads to the loss of two [[Royal Navy]] [[submarine]]s with over a hundred lives, and damage to another five British warships. *[[1919]] &ndash; The [[Battle of George Square]] takes place in [[Glasgow]], Scotland, during a campaign for shorter working hours. *[[1929]] &ndash; The [[Soviet Union]] exiles [[Leon Trotsky]]. *[[1930]] &ndash; [[3M]] begins marketing [[Scotch Tape]]. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: Allied forces are defeated by the Japanese at the [[Battle of Malaya]] and retreat to Singapore. *[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: German Field Marshal [[Friedrich Paulus]] surrenders to the Soviets at [[Battle of Stalingrad|Stalingrad]], followed 2 days later by the remainder of his Sixth Army, ending one of the war's fiercest battles. *[[1944]] &ndash; World War II: American forces land on [[Kwajalein Atoll]] and other islands in the Japanese-held [[Marshall Islands]]. * 1944 &ndash; World War II: During the [[Battle of Anzio|Anzio campaign]] the [[1st Ranger Battalion]] (Darby's Rangers) is destroyed behind enemy lines in a heavily outnumbered encounter at [[Battle of Cisterna]], Italy. *[[1945]] &ndash; US Army private [[Eddie Slovik]] is executed for [[desertion]], the first such execution of an American soldier since the [[American Civil War|Civil War]]. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: About 3,000 inmates from the [[Stutthof concentration camp]] are forcibly marched into the [[Baltic Sea]] at Palmnicken (now [[Yantarny]], Russia) and executed. * 1945 &ndash; World War II: The end of fighting in the [[Battle of Hill 170]] during the [[Burma Campaign]], in which the British [[3 Commando Brigade]] repulsed a Japanese counterattack on their positions and precipitated a general retirement from the [[Rakhine State|Arakan]] Peninsula. *[[1946]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|Yugoslavia]]'s new [[1946 Yugoslav Constitution|constitution]], modeling that of the [[Soviet Union]], establishes six constituent republics ([[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Croatia]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], [[Montenegro]], [[Serbia]] and [[Slovenia]]). * 1946 &ndash; The [[North Vietnam|Democratic Republic of Vietnam]] introduces the [[North Vietnamese đồng|đồng]] to replace the [[French Indochinese piastre]] at par. *[[1949]] &ndash; ''[[These Are My Children]]'', the first television daytime [[soap opera]], is broadcast by the NBC station in Chicago. *[[1950]] &ndash; Cold War: U.S. President [[Harry S. Truman]] announces a program to develop the [[hydrogen bomb]]. *[[1951]] &ndash; [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 90]] relating to [[Korean War]] is adopted. *[[1953]] &ndash; A [[North Sea flood of 1953|North Sea flood]] causes over 1,800 deaths in the Netherlands and over 300 in the United Kingdom *[[1957]] &ndash; Eight people (5 total crew from 2 aircraft and 3 on the ground) in [[Pacoima, Los Angeles|Pacoima, California]] are killed following the [[Pacoima aircraft accident|mid-air collision]] between a [[Douglas DC-7]] airliner and a [[Northrop F-89 Scorpion]] fighter jet. *[[1958]] &ndash; Cold War: [[Space Race]]: The [[Explorer 1|first successful American satellite]] detects the [[Van Allen radiation belt]]. *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Project Mercury]]: [[Mercury-Redstone 2]]: [[Ham the Chimp]] travels into [[space science|outer space]]. *[[1966]] &ndash; The [[Soviet Union]] launches the unmanned [[Luna 9]] spacecraft as part of the [[Luna programme|Luna program]]. *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: [[Viet Cong]] guerrillas attack the United States embassy in [[Saigon]], and other attacks, in the early morning hours, later grouped together as the [[Tet Offensive]]. * 1968 &ndash; [[Nauru]] gains independence from Australia. *[[1971]] &ndash; [[Apollo program]]: [[Apollo 14]]: Astronauts [[Alan Shepard]], [[Stuart Roosa]], and [[Edgar Mitchell]], aboard a [[Saturn V]], lift off for a mission to the [[Fra Mauro formation|Fra Mauro Highlands]] on the [[Moon]]. * 1971 &ndash; The [[Winter Soldier Investigation]], organized by the [[Vietnam Veterans Against the War]] to publicize [[war crime]]s and atrocities by Americans and allies in [[Vietnam]], begins in [[Detroit]]. *[[1996]] &ndash; An explosives-filled truck rams into the gates of the [[Central Bank of Sri Lanka]] in [[Colombo]], killing at least 86 people and injuring 1,400. *[[2000]] &ndash; [[Alaska Airlines Flight 261]] crash: An [[MD-83]], experiencing horizontal stabilizer problems, crashes in the Pacific Ocean off the coast of [[Point Mugu, California]], killing all 88 aboard. *[[2001]] &ndash; In the Netherlands, a Scottish court convicts [[Libya]]n [[Abdelbaset al-Megrahi]] and acquits another Libyan citizen for their part in the bombing of [[Pan Am Flight 103]] over [[Lockerbie]], Scotland in 1988. *[[2009]] &ndash; In [[Kenya]], at least 113 people are killed and over 200 injured following an [[Molo fire|oil spillage ignition]] in [[Molo, Kenya|Molo]], days after [[2009 Nakumatt supermarket fire|a massive fire]] at a [[Nakumatt]] supermarket in [[Nairobi]] killed at least 25 people. *[[2012]] &ndash; The [[Toyota Corolla]] is known as the best-selling car of all time. Selling over 37.5 million units. *[[2018]] &ndash; [[Blue moon]] and a [[January 2018 lunar eclipse|total lunar eclipse]]
