{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox film | name = Kartavyam | image = | caption = | director = Mohan Gandhi | producer = [[A. M. Rathnam]] | writer = [[Paruchuri Brothers]] | screenplay = Mohan Gandhi | starring = {{unbulleted list|[[Vijayashanti]]|[[Vinod Kumar (actor)|Vinod Kumar]]|[[Nirmalamma]]|[[Charan Raj]]|[[Uday Prakash (actor)|Uday Prakash]]}} | music = [[Raj-Koti]] | cinematography = [[Prasad Babu]] | editing = Gautam Raju | distributor = | released = {{Film date|1990}} | runtime = 2 hours 30 minutes | country = | budget = | language = [[Telugu language|Telugu]] }} '''''Kartavyam''''' is a 1990 Telugu [[political film|political]] [[action drama]] film directed by Mohan Gandhi. The film was a blockbuster and was subsequently dubbed into [[Tamil language|Tamil]] as ''[[Vyjayanthi IPS]]''. The lead actress Vijayashanti won the [[National Film Award for Best Actress]] for her performance in this film.<ref>http://www.telugunagar.com/Telugu-Movies/Kartavyam</ref> The film was written by [[Paruchuri Brothers]] and is roughly based on the real-life story of [[Kiran Bedi]], IPS Officer.<ref name="paruchuripolitical">[http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/political-content-dominates-their-films/article651505.ece Political content dominates their films: The Hindu Interview], The Hindu.</ref> The film was premiered at the 14th [[International Film Festival of India]] in the mainstream section.<ref>http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/Frm14IIFAAward.aspx?PdfName=14IIFA.pdf</ref>
